1
00:00:07,970 --> 00:00:10,220
I’m Ai, Gen’s girlfriend.

2
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:12,110
See you at home.

3
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,520
Can humans really have feelings for a robot?

4
00:00:21,390 --> 00:00:22,820
Something I wanted to give you.

5
00:00:23,770 --> 00:00:25,930
I want to visit the exhibition
at the gallery again.

6
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:28,180
I want to take your photo there.

7
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:31,800
Are you almost done?
My face is cramping from smiling.

8
00:00:32,610 --> 00:00:33,370
What's wrong?

9
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:58,340
Are you almost done?
My face is cramping from smiling.

10
00:00:58,530 --> 00:01:00,400
Almost done.
Just a little longer.

11
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:11,539
Ai? What's wrong?

12
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,530
Ai, you...

13
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:38,579
Miss! Wait!

14
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:41,380
Ai, stay right here.
Do not move, okay?

15
00:03:41,829 --> 00:03:42,670
Yes.

16
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:43,750
Miss!

17
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,160
Just pull up to the front.

18
00:04:01,370 --> 00:04:03,130
Please wait! Let’s talk.

19
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:09,040
They look… so much alike.

20
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:14,520
Ai?

21
00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:17,339
Please let go of my hand.

22
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,130
Who are you?

23
00:04:24,470 --> 00:04:25,770
I should be the one asking that.

24
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,840
Who are you to suddenly grab me like that?

25
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:33,400
I’m sorry, but you look exactly like my friend.

26
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:35,680
So?

27
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:39,909
I mean, didn't you notice?
You two look like identical twins.

28
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,370
But I don’t have a twin.

29
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,360
And I don’t know you either.

30
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,800
Can I go now?

31
00:04:47,659 --> 00:04:48,680
W-Wait a minute!

32
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:52,860
Why aren't you surprised at all
that two people look so much alike?

33
00:04:54,070 --> 00:04:55,540
Because I'm not interested.

34
00:04:56,330 --> 00:04:57,390
Am I free to go now?

35
00:04:57,420 --> 00:04:59,360
No, no. Hold on. Let’s talk first.

36
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:02,380
Could you at least go see my friend?
Please.

37
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,640
I have something to take care of.
If you’ll excuse me.

38
00:05:26,470 --> 00:05:27,350
Even their wrists...

39
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,340
are the same size.

40
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:41,460
Is it possible for two people
to look this much alike?

41
00:05:42,659 --> 00:05:45,070
Or is she another robot?

42
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:49,380
No. The way she talks feels too human.

43
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:52,990
Ah!

44
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,060
Gen.

45
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:33,580
Are you angry that I moved?
I’m back where I was.

46
00:06:43,590 --> 00:06:45,010
Now this feels right.

47
00:06:47,590 --> 00:06:50,920
I’m already standing right.
Even my angle is right.

48
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:59,670
You silly girl.
How can you be so naive?

49
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:06,760
So...

50
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:10,610
do you know the woman from earlier?

51
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:17,270
No. I was just wondering
why she looks so much like you.

52
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:21,640
Then which one do you like more?

53
00:07:23,490 --> 00:07:24,860
What kind of question is that?

54
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:27,480
Because we look alike.

55
00:07:31,030 --> 00:07:32,040
Take that!

56
00:07:32,510 --> 00:07:35,290
How could I like a stranger?
I don’t know her.

57
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:36,730
Of course I like—

58
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:41,240
What is it?

59
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,880
You didn’t finish your sentence.

60
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,270
Does that mean you like me?

61
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,570
I don’t know.

62
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,750
Aren't you coming home?

63
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,610
You haven’t told me I can move yet.

64
00:08:10,150 --> 00:08:12,580
Now this is more like you.

65
00:08:15,380 --> 00:08:16,500
I feel so much better.

66
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:34,010
Give me that.

67
00:08:36,909 --> 00:08:38,250
Are you really a robot?

68
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:42,429
Aren’t robots supposed to be strong,
made of indestructible vibranium?

69
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:45,120
But look at you. You looked
like your arm was about to fall off

70
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:46,140
over just a few bags.

71
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:51,150
Vibranium is a fictional metal
that only appears in cinematic universe.

72
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:52,240
It doesn’t exist.

73
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:55,210
You need to stop confusing movies with reality.

74
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:57,430
Hmm... getting bold now, aren’t you?

75
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:01,950
I was created to satisfy my user.

76
00:09:02,110 --> 00:09:06,030
I’m designed to be as human-like
as possible, not a combat robot.

77
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,730
- Excuses.
- You’re mocking me.

78
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:10,180
You’re getting good at talking back, huh?

79
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,640
You taught me that.

80
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:13,560
Oh really?

81
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,800
What? You’re making that cat sound again.

82
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,540
What? What are you doing, Ai?

83
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,980
Why are you taking pictures?

84
00:09:21,370 --> 00:09:23,750
They’re evidence that I was bullied by a human.

85
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:25,510
When did I ever bully you?
Give it here.

86
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,060
I’ll take your picture.

87
00:09:27,090 --> 00:09:28,390
- Want a Gen Z-style shot?
- Ai Josh.

88
00:09:28,410 --> 00:09:29,990
- I didn’t bully anyone.
- Well? Well?

89
00:09:30,020 --> 00:09:32,420
What? What? What? What? What?

90
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,370
- That’s enough.
- Got a problem?

91
00:09:33,390 --> 00:09:35,120
Whoa, P’ Gen.

92
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:37,040
You’re really going all lovey-dovey…

93
00:09:37,070 --> 00:09:39,210
- …without caring about the neighbors.
- What?

94
00:09:39,230 --> 00:09:42,290
Ever since you got a girlfriend, you’ve
become what? X... X... something?

95
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,390
Jeez, Auntie.
You’re such a pervert.

96
00:09:44,530 --> 00:09:45,680
Pervert your ass.

97
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:47,970
That word you kids always use!
Something with "vert."

98
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:50,580
Introvert. Extrovert.

99
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:52,250
Yeah, that’s it!

100
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:56,110
You’ve become... an extrovert now, Gen.

101
00:09:56,130 --> 00:09:58,380
Jeez. Wanna tease the kids
but don’t even know the lingo.

102
00:09:58,410 --> 00:10:03,280
See, P’ Gen, what Auntie's trying to
say is, no one ever visited your place.

103
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,380
But now she's having so much fun being nosy.

104
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:07,910
- Is that so?
- First your girlfriend, then your sister.

105
00:10:08,330 --> 00:10:09,620
Now even your mom comes over.

106
00:10:09,910 --> 00:10:12,250
- You having a family reunion?
- Who did you say came over?

107
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:14,070
Your mom.

108
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:15,670
You go deaf or something?

109
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,010
Hey, what’s wrong with her?

110
00:10:20,730 --> 00:10:23,960
I told you not to tease her too much.
P’ Gen’s mad now. See?

111
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:25,810
You think the mom and
the wife are gonna fight?

112
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,100
Let’s follow them to find out.

113
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:28,430
Not going to the market anymore?

114
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,520
The curiosity’s killing me!
But I gotta make money too!

115
00:10:33,710 --> 00:10:34,580
Let’s go!

116
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:35,910
To P’ Gen’s house?

117
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,100
To the market.

118
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:38,720
Start it.

119
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,440
Easy does it.

120
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:42,060
Mom...

121
00:11:45,710 --> 00:11:48,960
H-How'd you get here?
How long have you been waiting?

122
00:11:49,190 --> 00:11:50,430
Have you eaten yet?

123
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:52,620
Gen.

124
00:11:56,230 --> 00:11:57,570
Is there something you want to tell me?

125
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,390
Sawasdee ka.

126
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:15,950
This is Ai. She’s my housemate.

127
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:23,080
Hello, dear. Noo Ai, right?

128
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:26,740
Could you give Gen and me a moment?

129
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:36,280
You can wait upstairs.
I just need to talk to my mom for a bit.

130
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:46,310
Do you want some water, Mom?
I'll get you some.

131
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:47,370
Gen.

132
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:53,730
Is there something you want to tell me?

133
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:59,340
No, Mom. Why do you ask?

134
00:13:02,050 --> 00:13:04,180
Then when were you going
to tell me you quit your job?

135
00:13:09,220 --> 00:13:12,020
Are you surprised that I found out?

136
00:13:14,380 --> 00:13:16,200
I didn’t mean to hide it from you.

137
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:18,080
Didn’t mean to?!

138
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:22,350
Every time I asked how you were doing,

139
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:24,900
you’d just say you were
fine and had enough money.

140
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,050
You never told me anything.

141
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,060
If Kaewta hadn’t told me,

142
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:32,710
I wouldn’t have known anything
about my own daughter, would I?

143
00:13:32,890 --> 00:13:35,270
No, Mom. It's not like that at all.

144
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:37,860
So what are you doing these days?

145
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:48,260
Right now... I’m freelancing,
taking drawing commissions.

146
00:13:49,490 --> 00:13:53,440
But, but I get plenty of work.
I can take good care of myself.

147
00:13:54,650 --> 00:13:55,830
By hiding it from me?

148
00:13:55,850 --> 00:13:57,810
Without asking for advice
or telling me anything?

149
00:13:57,840 --> 00:14:02,710
Throwing away a stable job with
a good salary and a future ahead of you?

150
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,490
Why would you do this, Gen?!

151
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:07,770
Go on, tell me why.

152
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:22,140
Here we go again.
You refuse to tell me anything.

153
00:14:24,540 --> 00:14:26,370
- Mom, listen—
- Gen.

154
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,590
You’re the firstborn.

155
00:14:29,370 --> 00:14:32,640
I know you’ve never let me down before.

156
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:38,050
But if you can’t give me an answer this time,

157
00:14:38,670 --> 00:14:40,110
then go back and apply for jobs.

158
00:14:40,690 --> 00:14:43,970
I’ll ask around and see if anyone
I know has any good openings.

159
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:48,290
With your experience and qualifications,
you’ll have no trouble finding another job.

160
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:55,990
You don’t understand, Mom.

161
00:14:58,660 --> 00:14:59,660
You’re right.

162
00:15:00,610 --> 00:15:01,970
I’m just realizing now...

163
00:15:03,950 --> 00:15:05,850
I don’t know my own daughter at all.

164
00:15:35,140 --> 00:15:36,070
Gen.

165
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:41,470
You heard everything, didn't you?

166
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,720
I did.

167
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:51,440
Then you must’ve seen how pathetic I am.

168
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:54,070
I couldn’t even tell my mom what I wanted to do.

169
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:56,640
I couldn’t even say that I hated numbers!

170
00:15:56,670 --> 00:15:59,030
That I hated my job!
That I was miserable every single day!

171
00:16:01,020 --> 00:16:04,330
Even after I quit, I still had to keep
lying that I was still working there.

172
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:13,560
I just didn’t want my mom to worry.

173
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:19,030
Why didn’t you tell her the truth?

174
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,410
You wouldn’t get it.

175
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,690
Then tell me.

176
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:33,440
I need some time alone.

177
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:51,900
I’m going to make you proud, Mom!

178
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:56,160
I’ll work really hard and make
lots of money to to take care of you.

179
00:16:56,710 --> 00:16:58,120
I’ll hold you to that.

180
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,480
I really will do it, Mom.

181
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:03,170
Then you won’t have to work
so hard all by yourself anymore.

182
00:17:03,530 --> 00:17:06,270
I’ll study hard, make lots of money,

183
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:10,420
and take care of you and Joob so well
that Dad up in heaven will be jealous.

184
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:16,220
I just want you to have a stable job,
so you won’t have to struggle like I do.

185
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:18,540
Promise me.

186
00:17:21,690 --> 00:17:24,119
I couldn’t even keep a simple promise to you.

187
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:28,870
So how could I bring myself to tell you
that I just want to do something I love?

188
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:15,680
Hey, what's up?

189
00:20:16,180 --> 00:20:17,110
P’ Ploy.

190
00:20:18,420 --> 00:20:19,630
I have something to tell you.

191
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:20,740
Go ahead.

192
00:20:21,410 --> 00:20:22,710
I have to stop.

193
00:20:23,310 --> 00:20:24,330
Stop what?

194
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,240
- My mom found out.
- What?!

195
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:30,730
Are you okay?
Did she give you a hard time?

196
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:33,330
The thing is, she didn’t even say anything bad.

197
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:38,580
She just told me to stop and...
go back to a stable job.

198
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:40,510
So what are you going to do?

199
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:43,980
I don’t know.
I’m completely stuck.

200
00:20:44,930 --> 00:20:46,950
But I guess I’ll have to do what she said.

201
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:50,180
Just keep me updated.

202
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:53,290
So are you going to hand off your projects?

203
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,420
I guess I have to.

204
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,280
Okay, P’ Ploy.

205
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:02,240
Thank you.

206
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:23,870
Sawasdee ka, Gen’s mom.

207
00:21:23,890 --> 00:21:26,520
I’m Ai. I'm Gen’s housemate.

208
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,390
Hello. Is something the matter?

209
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,700
I need to talk to you.

210
00:21:32,580 --> 00:21:33,640
It’s about Gen.

211
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:38,480
If this is about her,
have her come talk to me herself.

212
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:42,780
Tell her that if she has something
to say, she should tell me directly.

213
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:44,600
Don’t have someone else speak for her.

214
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,520
Are you angry, Gen’s mom?

215
00:21:50,970 --> 00:21:53,370
I have to go to the market.
You should go home first.

216
00:22:02,130 --> 00:22:02,870
Ai.

217
00:22:04,170 --> 00:22:04,900
Ai.

218
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,600
Where are you?

219
00:22:14,870 --> 00:22:15,470
Ai.

220
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:33,530
Oh, dear. Have you been
standing here this whole time?

221
00:22:33,670 --> 00:22:34,860
It’s noon!

222
00:22:35,190 --> 00:22:37,440
What would you do if you get heatstroke?

223
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:39,970
Could I have a moment of your time, Gen’s mom?

224
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,250
Well, I can’t say no now.

225
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:45,520
Come inside.
You're going to get sick.

226
00:22:45,550 --> 00:22:48,390
Goodness, what a stubborn child.
Come on, get inside.

227
00:22:55,910 --> 00:22:57,000
Have some water first.

228
00:22:57,520 --> 00:23:00,090
How could you stand out in
the sun like that without an umbrella?

229
00:23:00,990 --> 00:23:02,050
No need to worry.

230
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:05,750
A temperature of only 38 degrees
can’t do anything to me, Gen’s mom.

231
00:23:06,890 --> 00:23:09,520
Just ‘Mom’ will do.
What’s with calling me ‘Gen’s mom’?

232
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:11,370
What a peculiar child.

233
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:13,790
So… 'Just Mom'?

234
00:23:14,450 --> 00:23:15,310
‘Mom.’

235
00:23:16,690 --> 00:23:17,810
Yes, Mom.

236
00:23:20,580 --> 00:23:21,910
So, what is it?

237
00:23:22,460 --> 00:23:24,700
What did that tight-lipped
girl send you to tell me?

238
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:27,560
You and Gen are so alike.

239
00:23:28,530 --> 00:23:29,540
What do you mean?

240
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:32,500
How am I like that girl
who keeps everything to herself?

241
00:23:32,970 --> 00:23:37,100
That girl is exactly like her father.
She keeps everything to herself.

242
00:23:37,410 --> 00:23:39,330
Sometimes I wonder if her mouth is sealed shut.

243
00:23:40,740 --> 00:23:43,590
She may seem stern on the outside,
but she’s actually kind.

244
00:23:43,890 --> 00:23:48,320
In biology and behavioral science,
this is called intergenerational transmission.

245
00:23:50,210 --> 00:23:53,030
You really are a strange one, aren't you?

246
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,510
So, how is Gen doing?

247
00:24:00,220 --> 00:24:02,950
She packed everything into
boxes and threw them away.

248
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,730
She called Khun Ploy and told her
she was going to quit doing art

249
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:09,030
and would have to find a full-time job instead.

250
00:24:13,630 --> 00:24:17,540
My duty is keep Gen satisfied and make her happy.

251
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,870
But this is something I can’t do on my own.

252
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:23,870
I can see that Gen isn’t happy right now.

253
00:24:26,810 --> 00:24:28,740
Do you want to see her happy?

254
00:24:29,660 --> 00:24:30,810
Of course I do.

255
00:24:34,830 --> 00:24:38,560
A mother wants nothing more
than to see her own child happy.

256
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:42,790
No mother would want to see her child go hungry,

257
00:24:42,810 --> 00:24:44,820
wondering if she’ll have
money for food tomorrow.

258
00:24:45,210 --> 00:24:50,040
Or if she’ll be able to keep up with the
mortgage before the house gets taken away.

259
00:24:51,940 --> 00:24:54,880
Just the thought of her crying,
of her struggling…

260
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:57,010
it completely tears me apart.

261
00:24:58,230 --> 00:24:59,890
Their father died when they were little.

262
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,940
I raised my two daughters all by myself.

263
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,720
I always worried about having
enough money for tomorrow.

264
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:07,040
And whether I could keep my two girls in school.

265
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:10,300
I don’t want Gen to have
to go through what I did.

266
00:25:12,340 --> 00:25:17,060
I’m already worried enough
about Joob and that video job of hers.

267
00:25:19,010 --> 00:25:22,300
Have you ever told Gen
that you’re worried about her?

268
00:25:29,790 --> 00:25:31,870
You don’t want Gen to draw, Mom?

269
00:25:38,110 --> 00:25:40,460
She’s really happy when she draws.

270
00:25:41,010 --> 00:25:43,990
Even when she’s worn out from
pulling all-nighters to meet deadlines,

271
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,870
Gen still smiles every time.

272
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:48,250
Then she starts thinking about her next project.

273
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,730
I can't do this anymore!!!

274
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:58,330
What’s wrong, Gen?

275
00:25:58,660 --> 00:26:00,710
I’m out of ideas!
I don’t want to do this anymore!

276
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:03,340
The deadline’s tomorrow!
There’s no way I can finish this!

277
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:07,830
- Then should I throw it away?
- Hey! Don’t you dare!

278
00:26:08,210 --> 00:26:09,240
This is my work.

279
00:26:09,630 --> 00:26:11,330
But you said you didn’t want to do it.

280
00:26:12,550 --> 00:26:14,030
I was just whining.

281
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:18,090
I’ll do it anyway.
It’s way better than dealing with numbers.

282
00:26:18,630 --> 00:26:20,920
Alright, let’s see how tough you really are.

283
00:26:21,010 --> 00:26:24,730
There’s no way someone like me
won’t finish this before the deadline!

284
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:34,050
Gen would always panic around 4 a.m. and say,

285
00:26:34,070 --> 00:26:35,660
“I’m not gonna make it!
I’m not gonna make it!”

286
00:26:36,130 --> 00:26:38,150
But by sunrise, she’d have it finished.

287
00:26:39,070 --> 00:26:41,350
Then she’d ask me to go
get something tasty to eat,

288
00:26:41,790 --> 00:26:44,140
saying it was her way of rewarding herself.

289
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:47,830
So what do you girls usually eat?

290
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:50,200
Instant noodles.

291
00:26:50,830 --> 00:26:52,760
Gen always says I’m not good at cooking.

292
00:26:53,690 --> 00:26:56,370
I can’t believe it. Gosh, that girl…

293
00:26:58,340 --> 00:27:00,250
You don’t want Gen to draw, Mom?

294
00:27:03,630 --> 00:27:08,290
I just want her to be honest with me
instead of keeping everything to herself.

295
00:27:09,390 --> 00:27:13,680
If she wants to draw, she should’ve told me.
We could’ve figured out how to make it work.

296
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:16,260
Never mind.

297
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:18,140
What else?

298
00:27:19,260 --> 00:27:22,930
Gen can still afford the house payments, right?
Does she have enough money for food?

299
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:25,140
Yes.

300
00:27:25,980 --> 00:27:30,440
She does complain that the electricity bill
is expensive, but Gen keeps the AC on all day.

301
00:27:30,650 --> 00:27:34,110
It’s no wonder it’s expensive.
That’s only logical.

302
00:27:57,870 --> 00:28:00,620
Gen, have you eaten yet?

303
00:28:01,870 --> 00:28:04,000
I'm not hungry, Mom.
You go ahead and eat.

304
00:28:04,740 --> 00:28:06,380
I still have a lot of work to finish.

305
00:28:36,810 --> 00:28:40,640
Finally... you’ve found your happiness.

306
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:55,170
Ai!

307
00:28:56,230 --> 00:28:57,000
Ai!

308
00:28:58,190 --> 00:28:58,880
Ai!

309
00:29:00,010 --> 00:29:00,690
Ai!

310
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:02,030
Ai!

311
00:29:05,060 --> 00:29:06,160
Ai, where are you?!

312
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:12,820
Ai!

313
00:29:13,940 --> 00:29:14,620
Ai!

314
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,330
Nong Gen! Nong Gen! Over here!

315
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,900
Have you guys seen Ai?

316
00:29:21,290 --> 00:29:23,150
She’s probably off smashing vases somewhere.

317
00:29:24,030 --> 00:29:25,670
P’ Zoon, that’s not funny.

318
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:32,200
You’re asking me? How would I know?

319
00:29:32,230 --> 00:29:35,280
Because you seem to know everything.
You even knew that a dog in Soi 10 died.

320
00:29:35,870 --> 00:29:37,510
Well, has Ai died yet?

321
00:29:37,970 --> 00:29:38,920
Watch your mouth!

322
00:29:40,950 --> 00:29:43,330
Forget it. Just call me if you see her.

323
00:29:46,890 --> 00:29:47,630
Ai!

324
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:51,260
Why is Gen getting all aggressive?

325
00:29:51,510 --> 00:29:53,350
- Like a fierce dog?
- Yeah.

326
00:30:02,010 --> 00:30:02,790
Ai.

327
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:06,640
Where on earth have you been?!
I’ve been looking for you all day!

328
00:30:06,670 --> 00:30:08,010
Do you know how worried I was?!

329
00:31:27,700 --> 00:31:32,690
“I think you’re happiest
when you’re drawing.”

330
00:31:57,860 --> 00:32:02,350
I told you before, didn’t I...
that I don’t understand human emotions.

331
00:32:04,140 --> 00:32:06,110
But when I saw your paintings,

332
00:32:07,070 --> 00:32:10,340
I could tell how happy you were.

333
00:32:13,730 --> 00:32:16,230
And I want you to be happy forever.

334
00:32:32,490 --> 00:32:34,190
Please don’t stop drawing.

335
00:32:39,680 --> 00:32:40,930
Am I still allowed to draw?

336
00:32:43,120 --> 00:32:44,440
Did someone tie your hands?

337
00:32:48,510 --> 00:32:49,330
No.

338
00:32:51,940 --> 00:32:53,370
Then keep drawing.

339
00:32:55,010 --> 00:32:57,770
And I’ll be the one to look
at every piece you create.

340
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:09,170
~ Now I know that good love looks just like you ~

341
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:12,100
~ I’m glad that we found each other ~

342
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:16,220
~ Your love feels like a dream ~

343
00:33:15,670 --> 00:33:16,800
Thank you, Ai.

344
00:33:16,230 --> 00:33:19,640
~ Whatever tomorrow may bring ~

345
00:33:18,860 --> 00:33:19,740
Thank you so much.

346
00:33:19,660 --> 00:33:21,840
~ Whether it’s good or bad ~

347
00:33:21,860 --> 00:33:26,260
~ I believe everything will be alright ~

348
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,430
~ Because I have you...

349
00:34:08,139 --> 00:34:11,030
Ai... I...

350
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,920
Do you have sexual desires, Gen?

351
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:43,159
Gen.

352
00:34:44,050 --> 00:34:46,699
- Gen!
- Ugh, leave me alone! I want to sleep!

353
00:34:46,730 --> 00:34:48,440
But you have sexual desires.

354
00:34:48,690 --> 00:34:50,590
- How are you supposed to sleep?
- Go to sleep!

355
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:54,380
You!

356
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:56,320
No.

357
00:34:56,340 --> 00:34:59,560
After studying 21,635 clips,

358
00:34:59,590 --> 00:35:01,160
- I’ve concluded that—
- Wait, wait, wait!

359
00:35:01,650 --> 00:35:03,600
What did you even study?!

360
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:08,470
I’m good at it.

361
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:32,980
You started this.

362
00:37:46,630 --> 00:37:48,350
Do you feel better now, Gen?

363
00:37:50,430 --> 00:37:52,040
What exactly are you talking about?

364
00:37:54,460 --> 00:37:57,530
Your mom.
What did you think I meant?

365
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:06,510
Oh, I see now.

366
00:38:06,830 --> 00:38:10,780
Basically, I experience physical
sensations almost like humans do.

367
00:38:11,230 --> 00:38:13,560
So, based on our intimate encounter earlier,

368
00:38:13,590 --> 00:38:14,650
- I feel that—
- Hold up, hold up!

369
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:17,000
Where exactly have you been today?

370
00:38:18,530 --> 00:38:19,750
I went to see your mom.

371
00:38:24,990 --> 00:38:26,910
Why don’t you try talking to your mom?

372
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:32,740
She won't listen to me.

373
00:38:35,290 --> 00:38:37,360
Have you ever actually talked to her?

374
00:38:49,670 --> 00:38:51,990
Why don’t you try talking to your mom once?

375
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:56,010
Tell her what you really want to do.

376
00:38:57,680 --> 00:39:02,420
Your mom might just feel hurt
that you never told her anything.

377
00:39:03,290 --> 00:39:04,920
You know what it means to feel hurt?

378
00:39:06,730 --> 00:39:07,740
Of course.

379
00:39:08,590 --> 00:39:12,160
I’m feeling hurt that you
still won’t talk to your mom,

380
00:39:12,470 --> 00:39:14,110
even though you obviously want to.

381
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,570
You want to tell your mom what you’ve been doing.

382
00:39:19,790 --> 00:39:23,640
Your mom worries about your financial situation,

383
00:39:24,950 --> 00:39:26,760
but you keep a budget every month.

384
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:31,120
You track every income
and expense, have savings,

385
00:39:32,930 --> 00:39:35,160
and even save money to send her.

386
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:38,990
You know too much.

387
00:39:44,390 --> 00:39:45,800
Please.

388
00:39:51,850 --> 00:39:53,310
Why are you doing all this?

389
00:39:55,870 --> 00:39:59,060
Because if I ever met my mom,
I'd want to do the same.

390
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:00,930
You have a mom?

391
00:40:02,390 --> 00:40:03,630
My creator.

392
00:40:04,700 --> 00:40:05,730
Besides…

393
00:40:08,430 --> 00:40:09,270
Besides?

394
00:40:13,140 --> 00:40:15,170
I want you to be happy, Gen.

395
00:40:18,090 --> 00:40:19,540
Is that because of your programming?

396
00:40:21,290 --> 00:40:22,220
No.

397
00:40:23,930 --> 00:40:26,700
It’s because you’re
the most important person to me.

398
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:52,210
You know...

399
00:40:54,700 --> 00:40:56,680
you're important to me too.

400
00:41:20,690 --> 00:41:21,870
Aren't you going to talk?

401
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:25,680
Didn't both of you say you'd talk?

402
00:41:27,780 --> 00:41:29,310
Your friend is quite something, huh?

403
00:41:30,910 --> 00:41:32,210
I think so too, Mom.

404
00:41:35,170 --> 00:41:38,070
Why are you talking about me?
You should be talking to your mom.

405
00:41:38,490 --> 00:41:41,340
If you won't say it, I remember
every word you've said.

406
00:41:42,470 --> 00:41:44,510
Then I'll say it for you.

407
00:41:45,620 --> 00:41:47,820
- Gen just wants to tell you that—
- No need, no need!

408
00:41:48,460 --> 00:41:49,380
It’s okay.

409
00:41:55,410 --> 00:41:56,180
Mom.

410
00:41:58,750 --> 00:41:59,910
I...

411
00:42:01,990 --> 00:42:03,070
I’m…

412
00:42:04,510 --> 00:42:05,520
I’m sorry.

413
00:42:09,150 --> 00:42:10,690
I was just feeling hurt.

414
00:42:12,150 --> 00:42:13,910
You never told me anything.

415
00:42:14,990 --> 00:42:17,070
I had to hear about you from other people.

416
00:42:20,410 --> 00:42:26,000
It hurts knowing that
my own daughter doesn't trust me.

417
00:42:28,500 --> 00:42:32,110
You just quit your job.
It's not like someone died.

418
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:36,240
Why did you keep it from me for all these years?

419
00:42:41,550 --> 00:42:45,070
I know now what makes you happy.

420
00:42:47,970 --> 00:42:49,020
I was just scared

421
00:42:50,130 --> 00:42:54,100
that you'd have no idea
what you'd be facing in the future.

422
00:42:59,740 --> 00:43:02,230
Actually, I wanted to tell you, but…

423
00:43:07,530 --> 00:43:09,000
I was afraid I'd let you down.

424
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:13,570
Gen.

425
00:43:14,740 --> 00:43:16,700
I might not always like what you do.

426
00:43:21,690 --> 00:43:24,110
But I've never been disappointed in you.

427
00:44:15,140 --> 00:44:16,470
Here you go.

428
00:44:16,810 --> 00:44:18,140
- Mom.
- Hm?

429
00:44:18,170 --> 00:44:20,010
Your daughter is sitting right here, you know.

430
00:44:20,370 --> 00:44:23,270
You be quiet.
I haven't even dealt with you yet.

431
00:44:23,650 --> 00:44:26,760
You quit three years ago,
and I only found out three days ago.

432
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:31,140
Mom, I already came clean.
Don't rub it in.

433
00:44:31,410 --> 00:44:35,240
If it weren't for Ai, would we even
be talking right now? Think about it.

434
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:42,920
I'll get you some water.

435
00:44:44,970 --> 00:44:46,550
I promise I won't burn the pot.

436
00:44:49,990 --> 00:44:51,550
What’s that got to do with it?

437
00:44:52,420 --> 00:44:54,090
Your friend is pretty cute.

438
00:44:54,580 --> 00:44:55,770
I know, right?

439
00:44:56,690 --> 00:44:58,090
She's such a goofball.

440
00:45:07,380 --> 00:45:08,670
- Mom.
- Hm?

441
00:45:11,420 --> 00:45:12,430
I love you.

442
00:45:26,750 --> 00:45:29,130
Here you go, your favorite.

443
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:33,250
If you ever feel tired,
come back home, okay?

444
00:45:34,940 --> 00:45:37,050
I may nag a lot, as is
typical for someone my age.

445
00:45:38,070 --> 00:45:40,720
But I love you two sisters more than anything.

446
00:45:47,990 --> 00:45:49,060
- Mom!
- Hm?

447
00:45:49,090 --> 00:45:50,520
I’m not a kid anymore.

448
00:45:50,620 --> 00:45:53,000
Oh? I won't comfort you then.

449
00:45:53,030 --> 00:45:53,780
What?

450
00:46:05,260 --> 00:46:06,550
Should we take a photo together?

451
00:46:12,440 --> 00:46:14,670
Alright, come on. Let's take a picture.

452
00:46:16,020 --> 00:46:18,530
One, two, three!

453
00:46:32,540 --> 00:46:34,110
Ai? What's wrong?

454
00:46:36,130 --> 00:46:37,250
Did she get me in the shot?

455
00:48:08,430 --> 00:48:10,360
Ai, go to sleep already.

456
00:48:11,970 --> 00:48:13,310
Gen, let go.

457
00:48:14,730 --> 00:48:16,280
What’s wrong with you?

458
00:48:16,950 --> 00:48:17,810
Sleep!

459
00:49:18,700 --> 00:49:20,140
- Beautiful?
- Yes.

460
00:49:21,220 --> 00:49:24,230
Wanna go?
I'll take you there when I’m free.

461
00:49:27,910 --> 00:49:31,190
It'll give the painting a softer feel,
and it'll be sort of like—

462
00:49:33,660 --> 00:49:34,830
I'll get it.

463
00:49:35,210 --> 00:49:36,920
- If—
- If it's the neighbors,

464
00:49:36,950 --> 00:49:38,850
I'll tell them you're not home.

465
00:49:39,310 --> 00:49:39,960
Good.

466
00:49:48,560 --> 00:49:50,580
Hey, Gen!
What the hell is going on?!

467
00:49:51,530 --> 00:49:52,590
How did you get here?!

468
00:49:55,580 --> 00:49:58,570
You said you were quitting,
and then you just disappeared.

469
00:49:59,170 --> 00:50:00,280
Of course I was worried.

470
00:50:01,050 --> 00:50:03,080
Who would have thought that…

471
00:50:07,520 --> 00:50:11,510
Sawasdee ka, Khun Petch, Khun Ploy. I’m Ai.

472
00:50:13,720 --> 00:50:17,570
How come your drawing...
turned into a real person?!

473
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:28,500
Any luck yet?

474
00:50:28,790 --> 00:50:30,250
We still can't reconnect the signal.

475
00:50:38,700 --> 00:50:39,710
The signal's back.

476
00:50:47,840 --> 00:50:48,840
What happened?

477
00:50:49,560 --> 00:50:54,460
It appears A382 shut off data transmission
two days ago, then reactivated it later.

478
00:50:54,580 --> 00:50:57,310
The signal was down for a total
of 48 hours and 23 minutes.

479
00:50:58,530 --> 00:50:59,540
On its own?

480
00:51:00,970 --> 00:51:02,500
- Yes, sir.
- It’s possible.

481
00:51:05,460 --> 00:51:09,470
It's possible the model classified
the situation as a highly private environment.

482
00:51:09,730 --> 00:51:11,110
So it activated safe mode.

483
00:51:11,590 --> 00:51:14,350
That means A382 is starting
to develop boundaries.

484
00:51:14,370 --> 00:51:17,980
It can now distinguish between
its own space and the user's.

485
00:51:22,340 --> 00:51:28,170
So that means A382
isn't just learning from humans.

486
00:51:29,940 --> 00:51:31,680
It's starting to make choices like a human.

487
00:51:38,660 --> 00:51:40,160
Prepare all the data for the meeting.

488
00:51:40,360 --> 00:51:43,860
I think it's time to bring A382 back,
wipe its memory, and hand it over.

489
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:46,320
But the experiment isn't over yet.

490
00:51:46,790 --> 00:51:50,090
We're only just seeing this new behavior
for the first time, and it's a good sign.

491
00:51:51,780 --> 00:51:54,230
If we bring it back now, we'll never know

492
00:51:54,260 --> 00:51:58,640
how far A382’s heart, which is
simulating human emotions, could evolve.

493
00:52:05,230 --> 00:52:08,460
The investor isn't buying emotions.

494
00:52:11,120 --> 00:52:12,780
He's buying something he can control.

495
00:52:43,890 --> 00:52:47,180
So basically, you submitted your muse
because you couldn't meet the deadline.

496
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:51,040
Next thing you knew, there was
a mysterious box sitting outside your house.

497
00:52:51,690 --> 00:52:55,160
You opened it and found
this beautiful Nong Ai inside.

498
00:52:55,400 --> 00:52:59,230
Whoa! You really got lucky, girl.

499
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:01,830
Speaking of which, I kinda
want a box like that too.

500
00:53:01,850 --> 00:53:03,600
- You’re delusional.
- What do you mean?

501
00:53:03,630 --> 00:53:06,590
Every guy has a dream.
I wanna have one too.

502
00:53:06,620 --> 00:53:08,530
You’re disgusting, P’ Petch!

503
00:53:11,740 --> 00:53:13,280
Is something the matter, Khun Ploy?

504
00:53:13,610 --> 00:53:15,200
There’s no need to be formal with us.

505
00:53:15,750 --> 00:53:19,240
You can just call us P’ Ploy and P’ Petch.

506
00:53:20,430 --> 00:53:22,030
Yes, P’ Ploy.

507
00:53:23,100 --> 00:53:24,330
- Gen.
- Hm?

508
00:53:25,040 --> 00:53:27,250
So, do you still want to send Ai back?

509
00:53:32,440 --> 00:53:34,130
No, P’ Ploy. No way.

510
00:53:34,490 --> 00:53:35,500
Hold on.

511
00:53:35,790 --> 00:53:39,060
Don't tell me...

512
00:53:39,500 --> 00:53:41,520
You’ve fallen for Nong Ai?

513
00:53:42,400 --> 00:53:45,190
I totally get it.
She’s this gorgeous—

514
00:53:45,220 --> 00:53:46,220
Shut up, P’ Petch!

515
00:53:46,950 --> 00:53:47,950
You talk too much.

516
00:53:50,270 --> 00:53:51,420
Is that true, Gen?

517
00:53:52,420 --> 00:53:55,450
Is it true, Nong Gen?

518
00:53:55,480 --> 00:53:58,510
P’ Petch! Shut up.
Ai, cover your ears!

519
00:54:01,020 --> 00:54:03,380
I can still hear you even if I cover my ears.

520
00:54:08,290 --> 00:54:10,610
Oh, she’s walking away!

521
00:54:10,640 --> 00:54:12,430
Are you blushing, Nong Gen?

522
00:54:12,450 --> 00:54:15,170
Come on, let P’ Petch see your face.

523
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:23,000
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.

524
00:54:23,180 --> 00:54:24,150
Oh, Ai.

525
00:54:24,170 --> 00:54:25,970
Remember the woman we met at the art gallery?

526
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,990
I don't believe two people could
coincidentally look this identical.

527
00:54:29,010 --> 00:54:30,750
I'll hack into the civil registry

528
00:54:30,780 --> 00:54:33,410
and compare your photos
to find out who that woman is.

529
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:34,710
Gen.

530
00:54:35,150 --> 00:54:37,150
Please look into it one
more time, I’m begging you.

531
00:54:37,860 --> 00:54:41,200
If there were two people who
looked exactly alike from head to toe,

532
00:54:41,430 --> 00:54:43,360
who would you choose to be with, Gen?

533
00:54:43,800 --> 00:54:46,000
Between someone who's
registered in the civil registry,

534
00:54:46,030 --> 00:54:50,530
understands human feelings, isn't
a health freak, can eat processed food,

535
00:54:50,560 --> 00:54:51,730
- and—
- I choose you.

536
00:54:56,140 --> 00:54:57,960
How would I know Ai won't be in danger?

537
00:55:01,820 --> 00:55:03,900
I'm giving you one last extension.

538
00:55:03,930 --> 00:55:05,780
Or I'll shut down your research lab.

